Series.Overview: Hey little one! Have you ever dreamed of exploring an island or travelling to the moon? Do you want to race cars and horses or to talk to a friendly bear? Or maybe you just need to hide from the rain? No problem! Louie is here! And with the help of Yoko, they will draw many exciting things for you to discover, right before your very eyes : a house, an aeroplane, a kangaroo, a rocket and even an elephant ! What is better, you can learn to be a master artist yourself!

Episode.Overview: Louie and Yoko are playing in the garden, but it's about to rain. What can they do? Louie draws a house and the two friends take shelter. But as soon as the sun comes out again, they can't wait to go outside and play some more.

Yoko is in the mood for playing, but it's raining and the animals have left. Who will play with her now? Louie draws a snail. Louie and Yoko play hide and seek, but the snail is so slow they fall asleep while they hide.
Louie and Yoko are exhausted by their walk in the desert. How are they going to get to the oasis? Louie draws a camel who gives them a lift and they drink the lovely fresh water at the oasis.
Louie has lost his scarf. Who can help him find it? The answer is someone with a good sense of smell, so Louie draws a dog. Before finding the scarf, the dog finds all sorts of things Louie had lost.
Louie draws some flowers for his mum, but feels they are too beautiful to pick so prepares a lovely flowerbed for her instead.
Louie and Yoko meet a sad and lonely tic-tic bird, who they help to befriend a rhinoceros that Louie draws.
After sliding around on a frozen lake, Louie and Yoko decide they need an ice-skating teacher, so Louie draws a penguin, who gives them a demonstration and teaches them to skate well.
Louie and Yoko are on the beach, but they are too scared to go swimming - then a dolphin shows Yoko the pleasures of the water.
Louie draws himself a car when Yoko keeps beating him in a race, thanks to her wings. When he wins, he decides to draw a car for his friend too so that they can compete fairly.
It's very windy. What do you do when it is windy? Go sailing, of course! Louie draws a sailing boat and he and Yoko climb aboard and navigate the sea.
Louie and Yoko are playing knights and princesses, but they are missing a baddie! Louie draws a dragon who is very enthusiastic - but he's much too kind to play baddies!

There are lots of leaves to gather up in the garden today, and Louie and Yoko are in a rush to go and play. How can they finish their work more quickly? Louie draws a robot to help them - then he wants to play as well!

Yoko and Louie see the moon bright in the sky. It's so lovely they want to go there and play. So Louie draws a rocket and they set off on a trip to the moon! The earth is so beautiful seen from above!
Louie draws an ostrich to help Yoko look for the marbles she has lost in the sand. But first they must scare the bird so that it puts its head in the ground.
When Louie and Yoko find a lone egg in a nest, Louie realises that he must draw a mummy for it - but what kind of egg is it and what sort of mum should he draw?

Louie draws a slide for the small bathing pool that he and Yoko are using so that they can have more fun. They end up having such a great time that Louie's little sister Sophie decides she wants to join in too!
When Yoko easily keeps finding Louie in a game of hide and seek, Louie decides to draw a chameleon to play with his friend instead - can she discover where a master of disguise is hiding?
Louie accidentally throws his ball into the pond and wonders how he can get it back - he needs someone who is nimble and doesn't mind getting wet - a frog!

When Louie and Yoko decide to sow some seeds but find the earth too hard to dig, Louie draws a tractor with a plough to help them with their task, and they are soon able to harvest some delicious vegetables.
When Yoko wants to play with the clouds in the sky but cannot catch them, Louie draws her a very soft sheep that looks like a cloud instead. But why won't the sheep let anyone pet it?
Louie and Yoko are collecting some nuts, but how will they crack them?
Louie and Yoko are playing basketball, but the net is far too high for Louie. He needs help from someone who can jump really high.
Louie wants to learn to fly and, draws an aeroplane. With Yoko's help, pilot Louie is soon doing loop the loops!
Louie and Yoko want to make hot chocolate so Louie draws a very kind cow, who lets them milk her.

Episode.EpisodeName: Louie, Draw Me A Fire Engine
Episode.Overview: Louie finds a little cat stuck up a tree, and draws a beautiful fire engine so he can rescue it.

Episode.EpisodeName: Louie, Draw Me A Sea Lion
Episode.Overview: Louie is trying to juggle, but he can't do it. He draws a sea lion to teach him how to balance balls.
Louie and Yoko have fished lots out of the lake, but how can they carry everything they've caught? Louie draws a pelican who offers to help.

Une hirondelle se pose dans le jardin de Didou. Elle est très fatiguée car elle revient d’Afrique, et cherche un nid. Didou dessine un arbre, pour que l’hirondelle puisse y préparer un bon nid douillet pour se reposer.
Yoko is singing very badly and Louie wants to help her sing in tune. Louie draws a piano and they put on a great musical show.

Episode.EpisodeName: Louie, Draw Me A Hot Air Balloon
Episode.Overview: Yoko is having great fun flying with a balloon. Louie would love to join her, so he draws a hot-air balloon and they go off on a wonderful journey.
Louie and Yoko want to draw a den, but it's difficult to carry all the wood. Who can help them?
Louie and Yoko are pretending to be big Indian chiefs but they need a horse. Louie draws a beautiful horse, but it is a wild horse that does not want to be caught.
Louie and Yoko want to swim in the lake, but a tree is blocking the way. They need someone very strong to help them move it.
The adventures of Louie and Yoko.
Louie and Yoko want to go sledging so Louie draws a reindeer. The reindeer pulls the sledge and takes the two friends on a wonderful ride through the snow.
Louie and Yoko would love to eat some bananas, but need help to pick them from the tree.
Louie and Yoko need a vehicle to take their friend, Daisy the cow, on a journey with them.
Yoko organises a tea party, but she's forgotten the cake. What can they do?
Yoko needs a castle so she can be a princess. Knight Louie comes to the rescue and draws a beautiful castle for his ladybird friend.
